<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--PastorJailed     07-22 0165</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Pastor Jailed,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Defrocked Pastor Jailed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A defrocked Lutheran minister and leader of a
radical protest group was jailed on a contempt charge following an
angry exchange with a judge.
   Daniel Solberg, 38, a member of the anti-corporation
Denominational Ministry Extended, was placed in the Allegheny
County Jail on Thursday after county Judge David Cercone found him
in contempt of court for repeatedly refusing to participate in jury
selection.
   Solberg, brother of actor David Soul, was to go on trial
Thursday on criminal charges of defiant trespass and harassment
stemming from a protest Nov. 1 at Nativity Lutheran Church in
Hampton Township.
   Solberg was pastor of the church for six years until a dispute
over his DMX activities cost him his pastorate. He was defrocked
two years ago.
   Thursday's dispute erupted after Solberg, who was representing
himself, asked Cercone to order an out-of-county jury to hear the
case and permit each potential juror to be questioned individually.
The motions were denied.
</TEXT>
