<1ST_LINE>r a PM-People-Madonna'sBrother     07-22 0223</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Madonna's Brother,0229</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Brother of Pop Star Charged With Attacking Woman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A brother of singer-actress Madonna has
been charged with attacking a woman, the third assault charge
against him this year, according to a police report.
   An arrest warrant was issued Wednesday for Mario Ciccone, 18, of
nearby Rochester Hills in the June 26 incident involving the
18-year-old woman.
   According to the report filed with Oakland County sheriff's
deputies, the two had been riding in a car in Rochester Hills, a
northern Detroit suburb, when they began arguing. The couple got
out of the car, and Ciccone hit the woman and threw her to the
ground, the report said.
   Ciccone, who is in Thailand where his brother-in-law, Sean Penn,
is making a movie, will be notified by mail to appear to answer the
warrant, authorities said.
   The other two assault charges are on hold until his scheduled
return Sept. 1.
   Ciccone is charged with assault and battery in an April 16
incident at a Rochester house, in which an officer was slammed in
the face by a door while investigating a noise complaint. The
officer required stitches and plastic surgery.
   Ciccone also is charged with assault and battery in a case in
Bloomfield Township in which he allegedly threw a pair of pliers at
a car Jan. 8.
</TEXT>
