<1ST_LINE>u p BC-CVN--GlennText     07-22 0928</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-CVN--Glenn Text,1st Ld-Writethru, a0822,900</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: Changes thruout</NOTE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the transcript of the speech delivered by
Ohio Sen. John Glenn introducing Sen. Lloyd Bentsen of Texas to the
Democratic National Convention Thursday night.
   Thank you. Thank you, thank you very much. Thank you.
   Thank you all very, very much this evening.
   I just knew I'd be making a speech tonight about the vice
presidency.
   And I am here to say this: Ohio Democrats will rally to this
ticket _ and on November 8th, Ohio will lead the way in giving
Michael Dukakis and Lloyd Bentsen the victory that will change the
course of this nation. Thank you.
   Now _ now I don't know _ now I don't know, of course, who George
Bush will choose as his running mate.
   But I do know that Lloyd Bentsen will be the next vice president
of the United States.
   And he is superbly qualified for the job.
   War hero . . . lawyer . . . businessman ... congressman ...
senator ... chairman of the Senate Finance Committee.
   And you want to know something? To get to the Senate in 1970,
Lloyd Bentsen beat George Bush.
   And this November, he and Michael Dukakis will do it again.
   And _ and they'll win because _ and that's because Lloyd Bentsen
not only comes from Texas, but he's a real Texan.
   Now we all know, we all here know that there are other people
who say they're real Texans, too.
   But let me ask you this question:
   How many real Texans do you know whose idea of Mexican food is
re fried quiche?
   And there are many other differences as well.
   This administration talks about fiscal responsibility.
   But their plan consists of the same old formula: more tax cuts
for the rich and more budget cuts for everyone else.
   Well, Lloyd Bentsen believes it's time we stopped asking this
nation to choose between fiscal responsibility and moral
responsibility.
   Lloyd Bentsen knows we must have both _ and he rejects the idea
that we should be hard on needy children, and easy on greedy
defense contractors.
   And Lloyd Bentsen knows that on economics, the Republicans have
it backwards: true prosperity always flows up from the people _ and
never trickles down from the powerful.
   This White House says there's nothing we can do about unfair
foreign trade that closes American factories and steals American
jobs.
   Well, Lloyd Bentsen believes that when other countries take
advantage of us, you can't talk like Rambo, and act like Bambi.
   And Lloyd Bentsen knows that with the right tools and a fair
chance, America can still outwork, out invent, out produce and out
compete any nation on the face of this earth.
   And when it comes to women's rights and civil rights, George
Bush is part of an administration that has consistently taken its
cues from right-wing zealots.
   They gloated about the temporary defeat of the ERA _ and then
boasted about appointing a woman to the Supreme Court.
   Well, Lloyd Bentsen knows there is a huge difference between
making one woman a Justice _ and bringing justice to American women.
   Let me add just another note here about the right wing. Let me
say that I am also tired of right-wing religious extremism.
   And of those who believe that they and only hold the truth. Now
on both things, we Democrats are willing to compromise for the good
of the country. But when it comes to the separation of church and
state, there must and should be no compromise.
   We Democrats treasure our churches and we treasure our faiths.
I've been an elder in the Presbyterian church for over 25 years.
But I'll tell you what I believe: I believe that the last thing
that this country needs is to have the gospels of Matthew, Mark,
Luke and John rewritten by Meese, Bakker, Swaggart and Falwell.
   Our opponents also talk about law and order _ and about how
George Bush will be tough on crime.
   But in this administration, over 100 officials have already been
indicted or left office under an ethical cloud.
   Yet despite that record, they tell us they want ``four more
years.''
   Well, I can tell you something: at the rate they're going, I
think some of 'em are going to end up serving ten to twenty.
   You know, you know, I saw Vice President Bush on TV the other
day talking about how Democrats are somehow ``soft'' on defense _
and that bothered me. In fact, it angered me.
   Lloyd Bentsen was a combat bomber pilot during World War II _
and he knows that we Americans must always be ready to defend
ourselves, because the very first obligation of government is to
keep our people alive, and independent and free.
   And if American lives are ever at stake during the next
administration _ whether in Beirut, the Persian Gulf or anywhere
else _ I can promise you that when major decisions are being made,
Vice President Bentsen will not be out of the room, out of pocket,
out of town, or out of touch.
   And I can tell you this: when Michael Dukakis and Lloyd Bentsen
tell us they will make ``no deals'' with terrorists like the
Ayatollah or drug-pushing dictators like Noriega, they mean no way,
no lies, no secrets, no deals _ period.
   My fellow Democrats, I am indeed honored to introduce a decent
and caring man, a good friend, a great senator, and the next vice
president of the United States _ Lloyd Bentsen.
</TEXT>
