<HEAD>Soccer Fans Riot in Bangladesh, 100 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fans of rival soccer teams fought each
other with clubs after a semifinal tournament match, and at least
100 people were injured, police said.
   The fighting broke out Thursday in the port city of Chittagong
after the local Abahani club lost by one goal to a team of the Sea
Customs Department, said a police official who spoke on condition
of anonymity.
   Police fired tear gas shells and charged with canes to disperse
the rioting fans, he said. At least five policemen were among the
injured.
   The official said 20 people were arrested. The tournament's
final match was because of the violence, he said.
