<2ND_LINE>PM-Rose Kennedy,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rose Kennedy's Family Marking Her 98th Birthday With Gathering</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kennedy family matriarch Rose Kennedy turns 98
today, an event her family plans to celebrate this weekend at their
cluster of houses at Hyannis Port.
   Her only living son, Sen. Edward Kennedy, D-Mass., is to fly to
Cape Cod from the just-concluded Democratic National Convention in
Atlanta for a small family dinner tonight.
   Also at the dinner will be Mrs. Kennedy's daughter, Eunice, and
son-in-law Sargent Shriver; daughters Patricia Lawford and Jean
Smith; daughter-in-law Ethel Kennedy, and an assortment of
grandchildren.
   Before dinner, Mass will be celebrated at home.
   Barring rain, the family might take Mrs. Kennedy out in her
wheelchair for some fresh air, Mrs. Smith said.
   Since a stroke in 1984, Mrs. Kennedy has been bedridden and
reportedly has been in poor health.
   Caroline Kennedy Schlossberg last month named her newborn
daughter Rose Kennedy Schlossberg for the child's
great-grandmother, but mother, child and father, Edwin, are not
expected to go to Cape Cod this weekend, Mrs. Smith said.
