<HEAD>Chinese Students To Be Allowed To Study In Seoul</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea's most prestigious
university is considering allowing Chinese students to enroll in
what would be another sign of thawed relations between the two
countries, officials said Friday.
   Prof. Lee Hyun-ku, head of academic affairs at the state-run
Seoul National University, told a National Assembly meeting that
discussions were under way on admitting Chinese students. He did
not give details.
