has an enrollment of 20,000. About 100 foreign students are
currently enrolled but none are from communist nations, Lee said.
   South Korea and China do not maintain diplomatic ties, but trade
and other non-political contact between the two nations has been
expanding in recent years. Bilateral trade reached $2 billion last
year.
