<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--SunnyvaleShootings     07-22 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Sunnyvale Shootings,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Farley Spoke Of Guns Before Seven Slayings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUNNYVALE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Richard Wade Farley talked about how he
might shoot up a defense company ``to wake them up'' about six
weeks before his alleged shooting spree there, a former co-worker
testified.
   Farley also referred to ESL Inc. engineer Laura Black as his
girlfriend, said Jerry Hirst, a computer technician who once shared
an office with two men who died in the Feb. 16 attack.
   Hirst testified Thursday in Santa Clara County Municipal Court
at Farley's preliminary hearing. Farley is charged with seven
murders and three attempted murders.
   His alleged shooting spree was motivated, Farley told police, by
Black's refusal date him after he spent four years trying to
persuade her to do so.
   Hirst said he thought Farley's comments were a joke. ``On
departing I said, `Well, good luck at finding your girlfriend.'''
</TEXT>
