<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Honda Recall,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Some '84, '85 Civics Called Back for Fuel Leak</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GARDENA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Honda on Friday announced a voluntary
recall of 279,821 of its 1984 and 1985 model Civic cars because of
a design flaw that could cause fuel leaks and what the company
called a small possibility of fire.
   Owners of the cars subject to the leak in the fuel pump will be
notified and the pump replaced free of charge, American Honda Motor
Co. Inc. said. The company said it had no reports of injuries
caused by the defect.
   The defect affects cars with carburetors and mechanical fuel
pumps. A crimped seam between the pump halves can begin to leak
after being subjected to internal pressure and engine temperature,
the company said.
