<HEAD>Minnesota Man Gored By Bison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK, Wyo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was hospitalized in
stable condition Friday after he was gored by a bison in
Yellowstone National Park.
   Yellowstone officials said Thomas Fox, 41, of Bloomington,
Minn., suffered cuts and puncture wounds to his upper right thigh
and a broken right wrist after he was thrown in the air by the
bison Thursday night.
   According to witnesses, Fox walked to within 6 feet of the
grazing bison, trying to photograph it. The bison charged and threw
Fox into the air, officials said.
   Fox was taken to Lake Hospital in the park and was later
transferred to West Park Hospital in Cody, where he remained Friday.
   The incident led park officials to repeat warnings to visitors
that all animals in the park are wild and potentially dangerous.
   Officials said visitors should stay at least 25 yards away from
wildlife and nesting birds and 100 yards from bears.
</TEXT>
