<1ST_LINE>u i AM-WaterTankCollapse     07-22 0188</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Water Tank Collapse,0194</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Water Tank Collapses; Three Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CIUDAD JUAREZ, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A water tank ruptured on a hillside
Friday and washed away about nine houses, killing three people and
injuring 17 others, officials said.
   Witnesses said the concrete water tank burst open with an
explosive sound Friday morning.
   The rectangular tank, open on top, ripped apart on the side
facing downhill. Police said it was at full capacity with almost 1
million gallons of water, and a torrent flowed downhill.
   Vicinta Saucedo said she heard a very loud sound and followed
her children outside when they went to see what had happened.
   ``I went out too, and saw a torrent of water flowing past,'' she
said.
   Martin Torrez de la Rosa, 9, said he saw a boy about his age
swept away in the water.
   He pointed to where he saw the boy and said, ``The water took
him away. That's all I saw.''
   Police said the identities of the victims had not been
determined late Friday.
   Ciudad Juarez is a border city of more than half a million
people near El Paso, Texas.
