<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     07-22 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Down Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell sharply Friday, weighed down by
declines on overseas markets and worries over interest rates.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was 14.8
points, or 0.8 percent, lower at 1,849.6 at midday. Trading volume
registered a light 233.1 million shares compared with 232.1 million
shares at the same time Thursday.
   Dealers said the market was depressed by declines on Wall Street
Thursday, when the Dow Jones industrial average dropped 24.01
points to 2,086.59 amid worries over rising interest rates and
disappointment with quarterly earnings reports.
   Declines earlier Friday in Tokyo, where the Nikkei index dropped
391.13 points to 27,285.01 also upset the market, dealers said.
   ``There are plenty of worries overhanging this market,'' one
equity salesman said, pointing to concerns over the near-term
direction of the dollar and crude oil prices. ``Until those
questions are resolved, we're likely to range trade for the time
being,'' he said.
</TEXT>
