<1ST_LINE>r f BC-MartinMarietta-Hoskyns     07-22 0227</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Martin Marietta-Hoskyns,0236</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Martin Marietta to Sell Interest in Hoskyns Group</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BETHESDA, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Martin Marietta Corp. said Friday it has
agreed to sell its 68.3 percent interest in Hoskyns Group PLC, a
London-based computer services company, to Plessey Co. PLC of Great
Britain for $190 million.
   The announcement came after Plessey announced earlier in London
it was offering to buy all of the Hoskyns shares.
   Martin Marietta said it had agreed to sell all of its shares in
Hoskyns to Plessey under terms of the agreement.
   The chairman and chief executive of Martin Marietta, Norman R.
Augustine, said the proposed sale ``is perfectly timed to maximize
Martin Marietta's return on its investment in Hoskyns and is
consistent with our concentration on growth in our core data
systems businesses of integrating information management and
communication systems.''
   Hoskyns Group, one of Europe's leading computer services
companies, provides systems in the manufacturing, distribution,
retailing, services and financial markets.
   Founded in 1964, Hoskyns has been operated since 1975 as a
Martin Marietta subsidiary.
   Besides information systems, Bethesda-based Martin Marietta is
engaged in the design, manufacture and integration of systems and
products in space, defense, communications, energy and materials.
   Plessey is one of the United Kingdom's leading high-technology
companies with annual sales of about 1.3 billion pounds, which at
recent exchange rates would be equivalent to about $2.2 billion.
</TEXT>
