<HEAD>Air Zimbabwe Orders Boeing Jetliner</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Air Zimbabwe has ordered a 767-200 jetliner in a
deal valued at about $66.5 million, Boeing Commercial Airplanes
announced.
   The order brings to 300 the number of widebody 767 twinjets
ordered worldwide, Boeing said Thursday.
   The new plane will be delivered in November 1989, with an option
for a second 767 to be delivered in August 1990.
   Air Zimbabwe will use the new jet to replace Boeing 707
equipment on its long-range routes, particularly into Europe,
Boeing said.
