<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-Armtek     07-22 0214</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Armtek,0223</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Armtek, Minus Armstrong, Continues To Show Earnings Growth</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Armtek Corp. reported Friday its
earnings soared 81 percent in the company's third quarter due
largely to the sale of its Armstrong Rubber Co. subsidiary.
   For the third quarter, which ended June 30, Armtek's net income
was $15 million, or $1.25 a share, compared with earnings of $6.7
million, or 58 cents a share, for the same quarter in 1987.
   Armtek sold Armstrong Rubber to Pirelli Group on May 31. That
sale and the disposition of other assets accounted for 57 cents a
share in the third quarter earnings, Armtek said.
   Armtek said sales for its three continuing businesses totaled
$238.3 million in the third quarter, up 15 percent from $206.5
million in the same period last year.
   Armtek's three remaining operating companies, Blackstone Corp.,
Copolymer Rubber & Chemical Corp. and Dayco Products Inc., produce
engineered drive systems, heat exchange components and systems, and
speciality polymers.
   For the first nine months of the fiscal year, Armtek earned $27
million, or $2.30 a share, double the $13.5 million, or $1.21 a
share, it earned in the same period a year earlier.
   Armtek has 21 plants in the United States, nine in Europe and a
joint venture in South Korea.
</TEXT>
