<HEAD>Cheaper Rent Pulls Sunbeam To Milwaukee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Allegheny International Inc. said Thursday it
will move Sunbeam's headquarters from the Chicago area to the
offices of its Oster appliance unit in Milwaukee, where office rent
is cheaper.
   ``Some jobs will be eliminated'' in the Chicago suburb of
Downers Grove, Ill., where Sunbeam is based, said Edward M.
Romanoff, spokesman for the Pittsburgh-based parent.
   He said it was not immediately clear how many of the 150
employees at Downers Grove will lose their jobs as the move occurs
over the next several months. The Sunbeam headquarters probably
will be reduced to a small office with about 10 employees.
   About 300 people work at Oster headquarters in Milwaukee.
   Allegheny International last month announced the formation of
Oster-Sunbeam Appliance Co. in a consolidation of its two small
appliance subsidiaries, he said. Oster-Sunbeam is a division of
Allegheny International's Sunbeam Corp. subsidiary.
   The move will not affect Sunbeam Corp.'s other divisions,
including the outdoor furniture manufacturer Almet-Lawnlite in
Portland, Tenn., the electric blanket and heating pad maker
Northern Electric Co. in Chicago, and the barbeque grill maker
Sunbeam Leisure Products Co. in Neosho, Mo.
