<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Gillette,0203</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gillette Reports Income, Sales, Operating Profits All Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gillette Co. on Thursday reported a 17 percent
rise in its second quarter net income over the same period last
year.
   The personal products company said its net income in the three
months ended June 30 rose to $67.8 million, or 60 cents per share,
from $58 million, or 50 cents per share, a year earlier.
   Sales rose by 14 percent to $864.7 million from $761.7 million.
   Profit from operations was up 11 percent to $146.6 million from
$132.1 million during the quarter.
   For the first six months of the year, Gillette's net income rose
27 percent to $143.1 million, or $1.25 per share, from $113
million, or 98 cents per share. First half sales rose to $1.77
billion from $1.52 billion in first half 1987.
   Profit from operations rose to $310.5 million in the first half
from $258.6 million a year earlier.
   One-time charges over both the quarter and six-month periods
included a provision for proxy contest expenses. Gillette purchased
3.7 million of its shares during May and June in fighting a
takeover attempt by the Coniston Group.
</TEXT>
